Tsang Says Intervention Needed When Home Prices Unaffordable

-- B y   S o p h i e   L e u n g
-- 
2011-10-12T03:17:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/tsang-says-intervention-needed-when-home-prices-unaffordable.html
Hong Kong  Chief Executive  Donald
Tsang  said the government will need to intervene in the home
market when prices are unaffordable.  The lack of supply of smaller apartments and properties
with lower prices have hurt residents, he said in his annual
policy address.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sophie Leung in Hong Kong at 
